ploswater: A dataset of papers from PLOS Water journal

Source: R/ploswater.R
ploswater.Rd

This dataset includes data on papers published in the PLOS Water journal. All raw data is obtained using the OpenAlex API. The data includes details on the publication, references, authorship, and institutions.

Usage

ploswater

Format

A tibble with 240 rows and 1506 variables

id

Unique Identifier

doi

DOI of the study

title

Title of the study

display_name

Displayed Name in OpenAlex

publication_year

Year of publication

publication_date

Date of publication

language

Original publication language

type

Indicates the type of scholarly work

type_crossref

The work type as specified by Crossref

indexed_in
authorships

Contains detailed information about authors and their institutional affiliations

institution_assertions

Information about institutional affiliations

countries_distinct_count

Total number of unique country codes among the work's authorships

institutions_distinct_count

Total number of unique institutions among the work's authorships

corresponding_author_ids

List of OpenAlex IDs for corresponding authors

corresponding_institution_ids

List of OpenAlex IDs for institutions of corresponding authors

fwci

Field-weighted Citation Impact, calculated as the ratio of citations received to citations expected in the publication year and three following years

has_fulltext

Boolean indicating if the full text is searchable in OpenAlex

fulltext_origin

Indicates how the full text was obtained (e.g., "pdf" or "ngrams") when has_fulltext is true

cited_by_count

Number of times the work has been cited

is_retracted

Wether study was retracted or not

is_paratext
topics
keywords

Keywords in the text

concepts

Key concepts in the text

mesh
locations_count

Number of different places where the work can be found

locations

List of all places where the work exists, including journals, proceedings, repositories (like arXiv), and institutional repositories

sustainable_development_goals

Classifications linking the work to UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)

grants

Information about research funding and grants associated with the work

datasets

Associated research datasets

versions

Different versions of the work available across locations (e.g., peer-reviewed published version, preprint version)

referenced_works_count

Number of works this work cites

referenced_works

List of works cited by this work

related_works

Works that are related to this one

cited_by_api_url

URL to access the list of works citing this work

counts_by_year

Year-by-year breakdown of citation counts, excluding citations older than ten years

updated_date

ISO 8601 date string showing when the record was last modified

created_date

ISO 8601 date string indicating when the work was first added to OpenAlex

ids.openalex

The primary identifier in OpenAlex

ids.doi

The Digital Object Identifier, serving as the Canonical External ID
